    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-12-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-12-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="277" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                <head>No. 6.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Comyn</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Earl of
                                Derby</gloss>.—(Received December</hi> 16.)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-12-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 14,
                                    1874</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: In conformity with the orders received
                            from my government, I have the honor of inclosing herewith a check drawn
                            with this day’s date upon Messrs. Frederick Huth &amp; Co., of this
                            city, to the order of your excellency as principal secretary of state
                            for foreign affairs, for the sum of £6,700 sterling, agreed upon for the
                            settlement of the affair of the steamer Virginius.</p>
                <p>I beg that your excellency will be pleased to acknowledge the receipt of
                            the said sum.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JUAN S. COMYN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
